          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Roll the<strong> lime<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span> </strong>with your hand on a hard surface (to release more juice) and cut in half</p><p>Add the<strong> chopped cherry tomatoes</strong>, <strong>diced red onion</strong>,<strong> chopped chilli</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!), the <strong>chopped coriander </strong>and the juice from 1/2 <span class=\"text-danger\">[1]</span> <strong>lime</strong> to a small bowl</p><p>Add 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong>, season with a generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and give everything a good mix up – this is your <strong>zingy</strong> <strong>salsa</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
